Project requirements

I have met the requirements related to working with GitHub and GitHub pages as my GitHub stats220 repo contains the required files:

  • README.md
  • .nojekyll
  • index.html

and lastly, this reports HTML file. My GitHub Pages have been set up and my website is accessible.

Link to my repo: https://github.com/JoannaKim3/stats220.git

Link to my website: https://joannakim3.github.io/stats220/

In this project, I used the Magick package in R to create both a meme and an animated GIF. To enhance the user experience on my website, I incorporated CSS to style my HTML output. This included personalising the design by adding a background color, selecting font family and color for headings and captions, and adding borders to images and the animated GIF. These details were chosen to demonstrate creativity and thoughtfulness.

I maintained a well-organized and commented code to ensure ease of comprehension. My CSS implementation involved applying a solid black 5-pixel border to all images through the img selector. Similarly, I added a 10-pixel solid black border to both the meme and animated GIF using relevant selectors. The font family, color, and size were also adjusted for my headers. I utilized a soft pink color for the background, bright pink color for headings and subtitles, and black for image borders. The playful Yusei Magic font was incorporated to complement the lighthearted content. Overall, I made these CSS choices to make my HTML document more visually appealing and engaging which I thought added more creativity.

Additionally, I added more functions from the magick package than required such as:

  • image_resize()
  • image_border()
  • image_composite()
  • image_text()
  • image_composite()

These functions were selected to enhance visual appeal and engagement.

Learning reflection

An important idea I learned from Module 1: Creating HTML by combining modern technologies, and whilst creating this project is the use of the R magick package. It is a powerful tool that can manipulate and combine multiple images, adds text, resizes, and creates visual content for websites. By incorporating CSS styling, it makes it much more appealing and engaging to viewers which is crucial in web making and creating HTML content.

Another key idea I have learned is using comments and well-organised code. It really helped clarify what I was coding for each section, keep track, and find my mistakes. Not only did it help me in my project to create my meme and animation, but it will also be easier for others when trying to read and understand my code.
